commit_message:
Add ability to cache swift temporary URLs

Caching of swift temporary is only useful for ironic python agent in
case of using proxies to download instance image.

This change adds the following:
- caching of temp URLs, so that proxy server does not invalidate the
  cached image for every deployment.
- [glance]swift_temp_url_expected_download_start_delay option, so
  that it is not possible to set swift_temp_url_duration less than
  the value specified. This option is also used to determine if
  cached temp URL will be still valid when agent ramdisk starts up.
  To preserve current behavior, this value is set to 0.

Partial-bug: #1526222

Change-Id: If79bc0067db92c8917a15a0989143a1133ad4519

commit_message:
Add RFC2616 formatter as a type for properties

The Date property of object_store uses a timestamp format from RFC2616
Section 3.3, specifically the first example. This change adds a
formatter that exposes this value, which is the transaction timestamp of
the request, as a datetime object.

The "date" property was previously only exposed on the Object resource,
but it has been applied to the Account and Container resources.

Change-Id: I0d4e0ab2e62bbe1e51eeeac98bfd819a2933f9a4

commit_message:
Fix authentication for non-session keystone.client.Client

Resolve issue where using non-session authentication (username/password)
fails to work with keystone.client.Client() as keystone.client.Client()
creates a default session object which then causes the
self.authenticate() method to not get called in the v2/v3
Client.__init__() method.

Change-Id: Ic0e5a4e735871921b9f13804e74b1233281cc565
Closes-Bug: #1539839

commit_message:
Use glance-swift conf for swift backend

For working with Swift backend, Glance needs authentication parameters,
which are supplied to Swift when making calls to its storage system.
Glance will use information from the file specified under parameter
swift_store_config_file. When this parameter is set to the same file
(glance-api.conf), we have lot of non-critical errors in glance-api
log, because of 'Invalid format of swift store config'.

The same problem, when we have RadosGW.

Change-Id: I18ee8f68f7ce793d2580685e79ed636556c57ddd
Related-bug: #1540890

commit_message:
Apply scheduler limits to Exact* filters

The DiskFilter, RamFilter and CoreFilter scheduler filters set the
resource limit on the HostState object during filtering. This is
later checked in compute during the claim, and used to enforce
the allocation ratios in a safe manner. The Exact* filters do not
set the resource limits, so scheduler race conditions can result
in multiple bare metal instances claiming a single host.

This change sets the resource limits on the HostState object in
the ExactCoreFilter, ExactDiskFilter and ExactRamFilter, ensuring
that only a single baremetal instance can claim a compute host.

Change-Id: I31d0331afc4698046a4568935a95f70f30e335dd
Partial-Bug: #1341420
Co-Authored-By: Will Miller <wmiller@cray.com>

subject: Failed to discovery when iscsi multipath and CHAP both enabled
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-02 12:56:59.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_volume.py'], 'message': 'Failed to discovery when iscsi multipath and CHAP both enabled

Storage server may be configured to protect target discovering phase with CHAP
authentication, in this case existing discovery command will be failed.
The authentication properties are:
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.username",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.password"
Cinder Storage driver need to send discovery auth properties in this case,
and the properties are:
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_method']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_username']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_password']

Change-Id: Ic70426d7d0fd8126879840f05341731ed92d6392
Closes-Bug: #1367189
(cherry picked from commit 45227bbbfd06d16e85e973e14ee8c30e267e8b42)
'}]
commit_message:
Failed to discovery when iscsi multipath and CHAP both enabled

Storage server may be configured to protect target discovering phase with CHAP
authentication, in this case existing discovery command will be failed.
The authentication properties are:
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.username",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.password"
Cinder Storage driver need to send discovery auth properties in this case,
and the properties are:
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_method']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_username']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_password']

Change-Id: Ic70426d7d0fd8126879840f05341731ed92d6392
Closes-Bug: #1367189
(cherry picked from commit 45227bbbfd06d16e85e973e14ee8c30e267e8b42)

commit_message:
Remove unused provider firewall rules functionality in nova

Provider firewall rules functionality is not in use and hasn't been
for a very long time. The api for this was removed in [1] and db api
methods for adding/removing rows in the associated db table have not
been used since.

Stop refreshing those rules as it is essentially a no-op and indeed a
costly one that includes a rpc round trip to the conductor to get
back an always empty db result. This should have a positive impact on
instance boot performance since the conductor call happens to live
inside an externally syncronized block of code.

Removes related compute rpcapi/manager code that were missed in a
recent cleanup[2]. Since this functionality hasn't been in use since
Havana timeframe(!), it should be fairly safe to remove without first
deprecating it.

Also removes the now unused virtapi method provider_fw_rule_get_all()
and the virtapi itself from virt firewall driver initialization.

[1] Commit: 62d5fae8d11b6403f9a63a709270ffafebb7ef09
[2] Commit: e6f7d8041783a0b3c740559d97b8d40b3568f214

Change-Id: Ifbb2514b9bc1445eaa07dcfe172c7405fd1a58f7
Partial-Bug: #1016633

commit_message:
Fix rsync service restart in os_swift

The rsync service is currently restarted using two handlers, one to stop
the service and a second to start it. There is not a sufficient delay
between the two task and so the rsync pid has not been removed before
the attempt is made to start the service.

This commit replaces the two handlers with a single one that will do the
restart in one go.

Change-Id: I8ed4630da1add7205552b6ec731a143dbe45112b
Closes-bug: 1538649

commit_message:
Return HTTP 400 if volume size is not defined

Nova API properly checks that in case of booting from a image to
volume bdm the client shall specify the size of the created volume.
However the API does not handle the exception properly and returns
HTTP 500. This patch handles the InvalidBDM exception and returns
HTTP 400.

Change-Id: I80d0aa64885f25081dad91b1f45da5b318d8ae25
Closes-bug: #1538197

commit_message:
Make the management interface MTU configurable

The default MTU for the management interface is sometimes bigger than
allowable by the physical infrastructure.  Make the MTU configurable in
cloud-init and via config json.  For cloud-init default it to the minimum size
for IPv6 if the value is not specified in boot command.

Change-Id: Ib4d4381f6977aabbeefd2f520bb5fc26ea54ffcd
Closes-Bug: #1539786

commit_message:
Use Swift venv Python interpreter

The use of activate_this to access the venv libraries means that the
system site packages are also included when the scripts swift_rings.py
and swift_rings_check.py are run.

This commit updates the interpreter directive for those scripts, when
Swift is deployed in a venv, to use the venv's interpreter.

Change-Id: I3ff0bf60c9ca695cddc28b05a8e8cc67d5f240e5
Closes-bug: 1538993

commit_message:
Fix warnings in glanceclient README

README.rst file for functional tests and glanceclient itself
raises some warnings when passing these docs through REST
validator and build the doc:
- Need additional empty line to provide correct indent in
cloud.yaml example
- Title should be with the same length as overline.
The patch fixes these warnings.

Change-Id: I2e2ef6f838ee639d1a88256b6e321181a62cc76b

commit_message:
Don't assign VIPs for GET requests

Since VIPs make no sense before a cluster is deployed
there's no need to assign them when network configuration
is generated for GET requests.

Co-authored by: Maciej Kwiek <mkwiek@mirantis.com>
Co-authored by: Roman Prykhodchenko<me@romcheg.me>

Change-Id: I382066cc62a9d98f728f5cd5edf771a5a980922f
Closes-bug: #1504572
Closes-bug: #1499291
Partial-bug: #1524320

commit_message:
Define self.client in MessagingCore

Currently self.client is referenced within MessagingCore,
but no definition is made in its constructor. Additionally
self.client is defined in children classes of MessagingCore.
This patchset defines self.client in the constructor of
MessagingCore and removes the redefinition in its children.

-self.client lazily loaded

Co-Authored-By: v-francoise <Vincent.FRANCOISE@b-com.com>
Change-Id: I14525a175bf1ebde3d2636024ad2f2219c79d6e1
Closes-Bug: #1521636

commit_message:
Fixed retries for server errors

The code does not properly handle situation when server returns http error.
Also added option 'retries_delay' to specify timeout between retries
Also disabled retries for 404 code

Change-Id: Ie5b2e720d453ef6e398400d27e631607b56e2937
Closes-Bug: #1539025
(cherry picked from commit 3677dc62e40d87811a4ed217958ef848a65634eb)

commit_message:
Remove LBaaS-specific devstack code

In Kilo neutron-lbaas implemented an in-repo devstack plugin.  However,
because of limitations in grenade, we were not able to remove the
LBaaS V1 devstack code at that time.  Clean this up for Liberty.

Change-Id: I3d9acf0da3aca58e706a9feb159f4e83b1c83133

Remove puppet resource for '/etc/swift/backups' directory

This directory is maintained by Swift package now, hence no need
to manage it through puppet.

commit_message:
Incorrect DNS servers definition in cobbler

At this point it is impossible to configure multiple DNS servers
during fuel installation because puppet uses incorrect template
to build cobbler configuration. This patch fixes syntax of
/etc/dnsmasq.upstream file.

Closes-Bug: #1491642
Change-Id: I2d4952e927104edc897771e0b754e0763d55fb0b
(cherry picked from commit 56fb819916f0c48c923fddf2dda58d2d7c9cc1ec)

Fixes for using the NFV Profile and Imports in the Tacker server

    usage, and added a test case

commit_message:
dockerctl: Add bootstraps directory to SYSTEM_DIRS

After backup-reinstall-restore Fuel uses bootstrap with wrong ssh keys.

dockerctl backup procedure does not save the bootstrap's root
filesystem, which holds the list of authorized keys that should be
matching the private key located in /root/.ssh on the master.
It would result in inaccessible nodes from a new master installation
(which has bootstrap images regenerated with a new key, not matching
the original one, restored from the backup).

This patch adds /var/www/nailgun/bootstraps/ to SYSTEM_DIRS list in
dockerctl's configuration file, so it will be retained during
backup-reinstall-restore procedure.

Change-Id: I3945200d02b29ed10e60900f7d03ed30970159a3
Closes-Bug: #1536198

commit_message:
dockerctl: Add bootstraps directory to SYSTEM_DIRS

After backup-reinstall-restore Fuel uses bootstrap with wrong ssh keys.

dockerctl backup procedure does not save the bootstrap's root
filesystem, which holds the list of authorized keys that should be
matching the private key located in /root/.ssh on the master.
It would result in inaccessible nodes from a new master installation
(which has bootstrap images regenerated with a new key, not matching
the original one, restored from the backup).

This patch adds /var/www/nailgun/bootstraps/ to SYSTEM_DIRS list in
dockerctl's configuration file, so it will be retained during
backup-reinstall-restore procedure.

Change-Id: I3945200d02b29ed10e60900f7d03ed30970159a3
Closes-Bug: #1536198

commit_message:
Switch auth_file URL generation to work properly

This fix actually passes a variable to openstack::auth_file
class which is using it then to interpolate it into
a string in openrc file. Otherwise we have an internal_url
which is improperly dereferenced and does not contain
suffix for the URI to choose the version

Partial-bug: #1533588
Partial-bug: #1539644

Change-Id: Ic3a70137e95df91c8e8fa257f16274e68075c800

commit_message:
Allow to build fuel/fuel-centos-build docker image through proxy

Building ISO through proxy is possible out of the box by:

 * defining http_proxy variable, for example
    export http_proxy=http://proxy_ip_address:proxy_port
    export https_proxy=https://proxy_ip_address:proxy_port
    export no_proxy=localhost
    make iso \
      PROXY_CONFIG="http_proxy=http://proxy_ip_address:proxy_port \
      https_proxy=https://proxy_ip_address:proxy_port \
      no_proxy=localhost"

 * allowing to bypass http_proxy variable for sudo operations, by
   updating sudoerc configuration file, for example:
      Defaults      env_keep += "http_proxy https_proxy no_proxy"

The only thing which needs to be updated - bypassing proxy for
docker build operation. This patch introduces this change

Change-Id: I2b5c7a071bec7448070395f88565701539a9adef
Related-bug: #1538698

commit_message:
libvirt: Allow multiple volume attachments

Add multiattach support to libvirt driver, by updating the
xml configuration info if the multiattach support is turned
on for a volume and set the virt driver capability
'support_multiattach' to true.

Also the attach function in nova/virt/block_device.py is updated
to call out to Cinder in case of each attachment request for
multiattach volumes, which is need for Cinder in order to track
all attachments for a volume and be able to detach properly.

Co-Authored-By: Ildiko Vancsa <ildiko.vancsa@ericsson.com>

Partially-implements: blueprint multi-attach-volume
Change-Id: Ib78fcd7c54c966dcbc143165a262e582bbda0901

commit_message:
Apply PAM security limits by running daemons through su

Daemons launched from OCF scripts inherit default resource limits. It
could confuse users and cause resource allocation fail under heavy load.

We should run daemons requiring root privileges through su - root -c, so
limits from limits.conf would be enforced. To make it easier to
implement, a new wrapper "ocf_run_as_root" is implemented in
ocf-fuel-funcs.

Change-Id: I4b0e0cd0ebca9013adbd69830ea79772014d6cf1
Closes-Bug: #1429553

commit_message:
Fixed retries for server errors

The code does not properly handle situation when server returns http error.
Also added option 'retries_delay' to specify timeout between retries
Also disabled retries for 404 code

Change-Id: Ie5b2e720d453ef6e398400d27e631607b56e2937
Closes-Bug: #1539025

commit_message:
objects: lazy-load instance.security_groups more efficiently

Rather than lazy-load the security_groups using the generic method that
has to get the instance from the database again, just use the helper
method SecurityGroupList.get_by_instance.

Partial-Bug: #1521675

Change-Id: Ie578967bf22288766b3acc2f7b4f55735e228b6f

commit_message:
Enable doc8 style checker for *.rst files

This patch is enabling the doc8 style checker for the *.rst files in
Ironic.

Since this patch is just the first stab at enabling this new check two
errors are currently being ignored by doc8 because of the number of
occurrences in our docs:

* D000 - Duplicated target names. We do have many links with generic
         names scattered around the docs (e.g "see", "link")

* D001 - Line's too long

These errors will be fixed in a following patch.

Change-Id: I32fb5a3104b9773c55a80a84dd81e49c567c76ac

commit_message:
Remove ntp element from overcloud images

NTP is now being configured via puppet, and the os-apply-config
template that gets installed by the ntp element actually overwrites
the puppet config, causing NTP to be configured incorrectly. We
just need to stop including the element and let puppet handle
everything.

Change-Id: Ia0680e57c026836cfa31a685b2e26d6a94f3e49f

commit_message:
SR-IOV: Fix macvtap assigned vf check when kernel < 3.13

when creating macvtap passthrough to SR-IOV VF in Kernel >= 3.13 an
upper_macvtap symbolic link is created. For Kernel < 3.13 the only
way to know it is by parsing the ip link show output and look for
macvtap[0-9]+@<vf ifname>.

This patch used the ip link show command to detects
macvtap assigned vf so that detection of macvtap assigned vf
will work on all kernels

Closes-Bug: #1523083
Change-Id: Icbc8d6af5c00d1453095e04dd779210dc7244c7f
(cherry picked from commit d7604169988726d121cdc9727accfeb6e29f4aed)

commit_message:
Add systemd notification after reporting initial state

This patch adds a notification for systemd after the agent has reported
its initial state to the Neutron server. This enables configuring
orderly startup of services that are dependent on the server having a
healthy openvswitch agent running.

Conflicts:
	neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/tests/unit/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/test_ovs_neutron_agent.py

commit_message:
Don't assign VIPs for GET requests

Since VIPs make no sense before a cluster is deployed
there's no need to assign them when network configuration
is generated for GET requests.

Co-authored by: Maciej Kwiek <mkwiek@mirantis.com>
Co-authored by: Roman Prykhodchenko<me@romcheg.me>

Change-Id: I382066cc62a9d98f728f5cd5edf771a5a980922f
Closes-bug: #1504572
Closes-bug: #1499291
Partial-bug: #1524320

commit_message:
Cleanup .lock files after package deletion from cache

After the package has been removed from the cache there is no need for
lock files anyway, so clean them up to save up inodes and cleanup
better.
This commit also fixes an incorrect file lock path used for optimistic
locking.
This commit makes try_cleanup_cache function more readable, by removing
unnecessary nesting of the code.

Related bp: murano-engine-package-cache

Change-Id: I727f020af44594bc12483a39480227ed9a0357bf

commit_message:
Include registry on update when other envs are specified

On an openstack overcloud deploy which results in a stack-update,
implicitly include overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml if the user
specifies any other custom environments. Do not include
overcloud-resource-registry-puppet.yaml if the user specifies no extra
environments.

This solution would be an improvement over the current situation, but it
isn't perfect.

It does the right thing when:
- the user does an openstack overcloud with no environments specified
- the user does an openstack overcloud with all custom environments
  specified

It will sometimes do the wrong thing when:
- the user specifies a partial list of custom environments (like -e
  do_my_custom_oneoff_thing.yaml)

Change-Id: I60fbf2182429f6bb83e000fc4d45269d7f83171b
Related-Bug: #1498607
Closes-Bug: #1504363

commit_message:
Allow to clean VIPs from plugins

This patch modifies merge policy in the way that
specifying an empty list of VIPs in a plugin will
remove all VIPs from the network role.

Closes-bug: #1524320

Allow murano to run under windows

windows. This commit restores ability to launch murano under windows.

Implements bp: murano-engine-package-cache

subject: Balance /var and /var/log disk partitions
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-01 21:25:01.000000000', 'files': ['iso/ks.template'], 'message': 'Balance /var and /var/log disk partitions

Prior to Fuel 8.0, there was a balance of the
following directories for remaining space:
/var, /var/lib/docker, /var/log

Now docker has its own pv, and /var/log was
incorrectly given all the remaining space,
leaving /var fixed at 10GB.

The new balance is as follows:
docker pv: 20gb
/: 10gb fixed size
/var: 40% of remaining space
/var/log: 60% of remaining space

Also raised minimum disk space requirement to
45GB. This reflects the actual minimum sizes
so that a user receives the error before partitioning
and is properly informed.

Change-Id: Id283e7dd4b94d5f6e1eb8397af33fea2b9f985f7
Closes-Bug: #1540331
'}]
commit_message:
Balance /var and /var/log disk partitions

Prior to Fuel 8.0, there was a balance of the
following directories for remaining space:
/var, /var/lib/docker, /var/log

Now docker has its own pv, and /var/log was
incorrectly given all the remaining space,
leaving /var fixed at 10GB.

The new balance is as follows:
docker pv: 20gb
/: 10gb fixed size
/var: 40% of remaining space
/var/log: 60% of remaining space

Also raised minimum disk space requirement to
45GB. This reflects the actual minimum sizes
so that a user receives the error before partitioning
and is properly informed.

Change-Id: Id283e7dd4b94d5f6e1eb8397af33fea2b9f985f7
Closes-Bug: #1540331

commit_message:
Consolidate ironic timeouts into one blanket timeout

Currently there are 4 separate timeouts used for baremetal
testing. This patch consolidates these timeouts into one
blanket timeout and replaces all occurances of the original
timeouts with the new one.

Change-Id: Idf2121c0b4ae3962109837b63057dac13df04fe8
Closes-Bug: #1526863

commit_message:
Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

Prepare babel-django.cfg qnd remove babel.cfg.
This repository is django related. Though django_openstack_auth has
only python files, it is reasonable to follow Django repos convention
in OpenStack.

This basically renames openstack_auth/locale/openstack_auth.pot to
openstack_auth/locale/django.pot to follow Django POT file convention.

setup.cfg babel entries are kept as this repository has
only python files and it still works.

Depends-On: Ie2462614ce92ee09a4d84481b4df9410f57f597b
Change-Id: Id817cdbe6925d505c183c555f5e59361b5d6fcaf

commit_message:
Add new conditions: matches and contains

Both check a value against a regular expression. The former requires
full match, while the latter requires matching anywhere in the string
representaion of value.

Change-Id: Ia59d17d6f8383aed97696d678fc1e7e329242692

commit_message:
Check missed ip6tables utility

In some scenario, like in OpenStack Kolla, system may lack
iptables-ipv6 package. This may cause command ip6tables-save
or ip6tables-restore invalid and ovs-agent error.

This patch allows checking ip6tables support from CLI:
    neutron-sanity-check --ip6tables_installed

Or using configuration options, for example:
    neutron-sanity-check --config-file /etc/neutron/neutron.conf
    --config-file /etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini

Change-Id: Ia6cf1ed6b5033442f03eac61d2d0d783c146d797
Closes-Bug: #1530042
(cherry picked from commit 34d4a6a78b288f87bd2f122a18916f940cc2b5fc)

Initially, we bumped the required version for the agent endpoint from
1.1 (the initial version that implemented security groups) to 1.3
without considering that the code should work with old agents that do
not yet know about the new devices_to_update argument.

Actually, there was no need to bump the version: old agent side code
already captures all unknown arguments that could be passed from the

https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/608b54137fb67512c07099089ea7e074176e12df/neutron/agent/securitygroups_rpc.py#L155

(^ the link shows the latest Kilo code as of writing)

Note: some people may argue that the approach that is taken in Neutron
to support backwards compatibility for server notifications is wrong,
and we instead should adopt some stricter mechanism like nova version
pinning. While that is a noble thing to do, it's out of scope for the
patch that is designed to be easily backportable to stable/liberty.

Note: some people may also argue that the patch should go straight into
stable/liberty because we don't claim support for rolling upgrade
scenarios that span multiple releases. That's indeed true, though my
take on it is that if we have a way to handle more unofficial scenarios
without more coding effort, it's worth doing it.

commit_message:
Make security_groups_provider_updated work with Kilo agents

Initially, we bumped the required version for the agent endpoint from
1.1 (the initial version that implemented security groups) to 1.3
without considering that the code should work with old agents that do
not yet know about the new devices_to_update argument.

Actually, there was no need to bump the version: old agent side code
already captures all unknown arguments that could be passed from the
server, ignoring them:

https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/608b54137fb67512c07099089ea7e074176e12df/neutron/agent/securitygroups_rpc.py#L155

(^ the link shows the latest Kilo code as of writing)

Note: some people may argue that the approach that is taken in Neutron
to support backwards compatibility for server notifications is wrong,
and we instead should adopt some stricter mechanism like nova version
pinning. While that is a noble thing to do, it's out of scope for the
patch that is designed to be easily backportable to stable/liberty.

Note: some people may also argue that the patch should go straight into
stable/liberty because we don't claim support for rolling upgrade
scenarios that span multiple releases. That's indeed true, though my
take on it is that if we have a way to handle more unofficial scenarios
without more coding effort, it's worth doing it.

Change-Id: I741e6e5c460658ac17095551040e67e8d1990812
Closes-Bug: #1531772
(cherry picked from commit f8f366024052a191eb0fc74af1643be15c541aef)

commit_message:
manila CI: disable CG tempest tests

The manila API tempest tests for consistency groups (CGs) also test
the 'create_consistency_group_from_snapshot' API that is not
implemented by the cephfs native driver. So disable it by default in
the CI hook script.

commit_message:
Use eval_generate instead of generate

Current override_resources implementation will not create
all needed dependencies/relationships (before, after, notify,
subscribe) for new resources (not defined in catalog).

This fix requires that override_resources MUST
be used ALWAYS as first resource in manifets.

We need to put that statement in documentation

DocImpact

Change-Id: Iac6541c6e7440cb9c4c87ee52cc178c548b19ad6
Closes-Bug: #1538526

Storage server may be configured to protect target discovering phase with CHAP
authentication, in this case existing discovery command will be failed.
The authentication properties are:
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.username",

Cinder Storage driver need to send discovery auth properties in this case,

commit_message:
Failed to discovery when iscsi multipath and CHAP both enabled

Storage server may be configured to protect target discovering phase with CHAP
authentication, in this case existing discovery command will be failed.
The authentication properties are:
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.username",
    "discovery.sendtargets.auth.password"
Cinder Storage driver need to send discovery auth properties in this case,
and the properties are:
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_method']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_username']
    iscsi_properties['discovery_auth_password']

Change-Id: Ic70426d7d0fd8126879840f05341731ed92d6392
Closes-Bug: #1367189

commit_message:
Fix changes domain name in MOS services endpoints

We couldn't use public vip ip before start deploying cluster.
So, we need to add option to skip SSL cert verification
when connecting to the MOS services, and replace unresolvable
domain name with public vip ip after deployment

Closes-Bug:1537833

commit_message:
Add support for property defaults

Allows the definition of a dictionary of properties in the glance
configuration which is then in turn merged with those passed to the
APIs.  This supports the use case where OpenStack is managing a
heterogeneous pool of compute hosts and images are scheduled onto the
correct host aggregate based on the architecture property of the
chosen image.  End users predominantly expect things to just work
without explicitly specifying the architecture, so this provides a
basic framework to allow defaulting to say x86_64 which handles the
common case.

Closes-Bug: 1519745

Change-Id: I2ac3cb98105b99458ebc51982ea96aa6a44b11a8

commit_message:
Fixed handling of None values for limit, marker and is_public when
listing images in client v1.

Currently, when images.list() is called in the v1 client, specifying
None for limit, marker or is_public results in an invalid value being
added to the query string, which results in an Invalid parameter error
from the server. This patch fixes this issue, making the behaviour
similar to other clients.

Change-Id: I91bb41109d1b19705c5673be15c86046e53b80ed

subject: Refactor: Join multiple criteria together
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-05-14 08:22:42.000000000', 'files': ['glance/db/sqlalchemy/api.py'], 'message': 'Refactor: Join multiple criteria together

Filtering criterion in the method of "Query.filter_by()" or
"Query.filter()" introduced by SQLAlchemy supports to join
multiple criteria together instead of join each criteria
separately. The motivation to make this change includes:

1. The docstring in the SQLAlchemy tell us the usage:
" Multiple criteria are joined together by AND::
   session.query(MyClass).\\
      filter(MyClass.name == 'some name', MyClass.id > 5)"
or
" Multiple criteria are joined together by AND::
   session.query(MyClass).\\
      filter_by(name = 'some name', id = 5)
"
Since SQLAlchemy provides this interface, this should has
its benefit from introducing this method, the direct impact
is we needn't build the query statement repetitively.

2. The change make the code looks more concise.

Additional change is to build queries in same code style, e.g.

query = session.query(models.Task)
query = query.filter_by(task_id=5)

replace with more common one:

query = session.query(models.Task).filter_by(task_id=5)

Closes-Bug: #1449850
Change-Id: Ifedf53fa0f7302c68acb8b1661779559e2be0d78
'}]
commit_message:
Refactor: Join multiple criteria together

Filtering criterion in the method of "Query.filter_by()" or
"Query.filter()" introduced by SQLAlchemy supports to join
multiple criteria together instead of join each criteria
separately. The motivation to make this change includes:

1. The docstring in the SQLAlchemy tell us the usage:
" Multiple criteria are joined together by AND::
   session.query(MyClass).\\
      filter(MyClass.name == 'some name', MyClass.id > 5)"
or
" Multiple criteria are joined together by AND::
   session.query(MyClass).\\
      filter_by(name = 'some name', id = 5)
"
Since SQLAlchemy provides this interface, this should has
its benefit from introducing this method, the direct impact
is we needn't build the query statement repetitively.

2. The change make the code looks more concise.

Additional change is to build queries in same code style, e.g.

query = session.query(models.Task)
query = query.filter_by(task_id=5)

replace with more common one:

query = session.query(models.Task).filter_by(task_id=5)

Closes-Bug: #1449850
Change-Id: Ifedf53fa0f7302c68acb8b1661779559e2be0d78

commit_message:
Quote vars when checking them on emptiness

Not doing so leads to bash errors when string contains spaces.
Specifically, variable OCF_RESKEY_CRM_meta_notify_stop_uname
can contain spaces when several nodes are stopped simultaneously
and that leads to error described in the bug referenced below.

Make rabbitmq OCF script POSIX compatible
Related blueprint upstream-rabbit-ocf
Closes-bug: #1473015

Change-Id: I1447f58e897cc1fe6b9884c3b4cd4f950dd9cecb
Closes-bug: #1527518
(cherry picked from commit fe4edc4589ff37647134fdf83fc4e8896469cdd7)

commit_message:
Use node uuid in some exception log

The error log using node id in some exception log is not
readable, like:
'NodeLocked: Node 16 is locked by host localhost, please
retry after the current operation is completed.'
Update the node id with node uuid to make it more readable.

Change-Id: I83a0adcc28819c44323276d65bc038da7808efac
Closes-Bug: #1537992

commit_message:
[DynamicUI] Apply user regex for the password field

Currently password field has strong regexp validator.
Previously it was not possible to application author
to soften password requirements.
This commit enables overwriting default validator with
a single 'regexpValidator' or multiple (dymanicUI special argument) -
'validators'.

Implements blueprint update-password-field

Change-Id: Id417ed71dcd737636439a2beb701751aa4ec0c12

commit_message:
Support to boot a VM with network name

Bug_description:
Today, in order to specify networking arguments, the nova client
only accept uuid's. It would be nice if we could extend the
client option to allow names to be accepted too.

Solution:
This patch supports provisioning of VM by mentioning network name.
_boot method currently validates for network ID to boot a VM.

Updates:
* new parameter 'net-name' is added
* when 'net-name' is specified network ID is retrieved
* network ID is used for further processing of vm boot request
* if multiple networks with the same name exist then
NoUniqueMatch exception is raised
* help text is updated

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1496180

Co-Authored-By: Pavel Kholkin <pkholkin@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ifb14a76749901ee106cdb807e38820a2c25e1320

commit_message:
Revert "Added new scheduler filter: AggregateTypeExtraSpecsAffinityFilter"

This reverts commit 4b142e53e43132e996d35c335da30959f9f361be.


I was having a point left unresolved in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/189279/8/doc/source/filter_scheduler.rst about the tech debt that adding a new filter in-tree would cause for something very closely related to another filter.

I totally get the need for adding more logic and reverting how we compare flavors vs. aggregates. I just feel that before committing ourselves to that, we need to correctly estimate the possibilities to modify AggregateInstanceExtraSpecsFilter to fit the above needs.

Change-Id: Ic9f70dae037d32980a5a252bdd08eff02ba27120

Add a migration and model for a resource_classes table in the api
database. A ResourceClass has a name and an id.

For sake of auditing the TimestampMixin is used to have created_at
and updated_at fields.

commit_message:
Add ResourceClassList versioned object

ResourceClassList provides a list of ResourceClass objects, making
it possible to list all the persisted resource classes in the
resource_classes table.

The unit tests are fairly contrived (too much work in the mocks)
so functional tests are also provided.

Change-Id: I3c971aa38580e71f356962af3ba67b3ac1882e12
Partially-Implements: blueprint resource-classes

commit_message:
Remove hard-coded DEPLOYWAIT timeout from Baremetal Scenario

Currently the baremetal scenario is hardcoded to wait 15 seconds
for the ironic node to reach the wait-callback state. This patch
adds a configuration option for this timeout and replaces the
hardcoded value with it.

Closes-Bug: #1526466

Change-Id: I8cded9467dc03d9e1a75222bb4b017604ae946af

commit_message:
rearrange content in preparation to move to new vhost

We want to remove the redundant 'releases' directory in the URLs for
release pages, so create one directory for each series and move the
existing file there. Sphinx doesn't have an easy way to handle
redirects, so just add a stub page with a link to the root document for
folks to find the thing that moved. We will delete these pages after we
start publishing to releases.openstack.org instead of
docs.openstack.org.

Change-Id: I970bdd20e23c748a7e8a456808c73d74570eb066
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

The default fixed_ip allocation always does .first() out of the fixed
ip pool. This leads to a pathological situation that in a rapidly
changing environment we're constantly recycling the same small number
of ips out of the pool. Given other racey behavior in dnsmasq around

commit_message:
Spread allocations of fixed ips

The default fixed_ip allocation always does .first() out of the fixed
ip pool. This leads to a pathological situation that in a rapidly
changing environment we're constantly recycling the same small number
of ips out of the pool. Given other racey behavior in dnsmasq around
processing DHCP Release requests, we can start to get DHCP fails when
a DHCP release is missed, we immediately recycle the IP and give it to
a new guest.

We can mitigate this by sorting the results by updated_at. This
means we'll favor least recently used fixed ips.

Depends-On: I27f73c1edf12218818c4d279efbd9fef5cdef672

Related-Bug: #1532809

Change-Id: I3c83bd68a0e2bbbcdd6d955722dbc9f9fc528113

commit_message:
Added new scheduler filter: AggregateTypeExtraSpecsAffinityFilter

The flavor_extra_spec metadata pair will be consumed by the
AggregateTypeExtraSpecsAffinityFilter to allow operators to define a
set of extra specs key value pairs that are required to schedule to
the aggregate, e.g.:
  standard memory backing aggregate:
    flavor_extra_spec: "hw:mem_page_size=small,hw:mem_page_size=any"
  high bandwidth memory backing aggregate:
    flavor_extra_spec: "hw:mem_page_size=2M,hw:mem_page_size=1G," \
                       "hw:mem_page_size=large"

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint aggregate-extra-specs-filter
Change-Id: Id3a9918cf9f83b2a9b1dfbcd91803b5b1b2bcc78

commit_message:
Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
python-heatclient/locale/python-heatclient.pot to
heatclient/locale/heatclient.pot. For this we need to update
setup.cfg.

The domain name is already correct in i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

Remove test for valid translation files in tox.ini since there are now
no more pot files - and the test fails if there are no files at all.

Change-Id: I6f5e77b9cd633f6edb503ff225ca0b507153946c

commit_message:
Remove outdated pot files

These files are outdated and not needed, translation is done using our
translation server. The current scripts work even when these files do
not exist. Once there are translated files, the files will be imported
automatically again and updated.

This is part of implementing the new infra setup for translations,
see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

Remove test for valid po/pot files from tox.ini, this is now done in the
infra scripts.

Change-Id: I49dded30597533434a7c751cdabf8b6a11e1c1c5

commit_message:
Fix changes domain name in MOS services endpoints

We couldn't use public vip ip before start deploying cluster.
So, we need to add option to skip SSL cert verification
when connecting to the MOS services, and replace unresolvable
domain name with public vip ip after deployment

Closes-Bug:1537833

Change-Id: I53621022a3ae55cb30ab224800fc812ce2b0a79b

This change prevents the pingtest from failing the ha and ceph jobs.
I'm leaving it voting on the nonha job because it is passing some
of the time and I don't want to let in breaking changes again.  It
should be more possible to get three passing CI jobs if only one
of them has to pass the pingtest.  The ping test will still be run
on the ha and ceph jobs, but if it fails the failure will be
ignored.  This way it's still possible to look at the results in

Change-Id: I9c983ff036fe9488abf2522a84e56f036f7fa61d
"}]
commit_message:
Make pingtest partially voting

This change prevents the pingtest from failing the ha and ceph jobs.
I'm leaving it voting on the nonha job because it is passing some
of the time and I don't want to let in breaking changes again.  It
should be more possible to get three passing CI jobs if only one
of them has to pass the pingtest.  The ping test will still be run
on the ha and ceph jobs, but if it fails the failure will be
ignored.  This way it's still possible to look at the results in
the CI logs if there's a concern about a change with one of those jobs.

Change-Id: I9c983ff036fe9488abf2522a84e56f036f7fa61d

subject: Fix for not running 'on-success' task after task with 'with-items'
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-01 12:17:38.000000000', 'files': ['mistral/tests/unit/engine/test_with_items.py', 'mistral/engine/default_engine.py'], 'message': "Fix for not running 'on-success' task after task with 'with-items'

The following bug is caused by using READ_COMMITTED transaction level. When
2 actions are running simultanously, this is what happen in default engine
when on_action_complete is called:
1. Action1 is marked as 'Success'; engine checks if Task1 has ended (it
has not, since there is still Action2);
2. Action2 is marked as 'Success'; engine checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success');
3. Action1 enters second transaction and checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success'), so it looks for next tasks
to run - it finds Task2
4. Action2 enters second transaction and checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success'), so it looks for next tasks
to run - it finds none, because of what happens in Action1 thread.

With this change, it is not only checked with DB if task has ended in
second transaction, but it also checks, if task was ended in the previous
transaction.

Closes-Bug: 1535722

Change-Id: Ifb2cfde4a88619b7664669f2d5ca14fa47379961
"}]
commit_message:
Fix for not running 'on-success' task after task with 'with-items'

The following bug is caused by using READ_COMMITTED transaction level. When
2 actions are running simultanously, this is what happen in default engine
when on_action_complete is called:
1. Action1 is marked as 'Success'; engine checks if Task1 has ended (it
has not, since there is still Action2);
2. Action2 is marked as 'Success'; engine checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success');
3. Action1 enters second transaction and checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success'), so it looks for next tasks
to run - it finds Task2
4. Action2 enters second transaction and checks if Task1 has ended (it
has, both actions has been marked as 'Success'), so it looks for next tasks
to run - it finds none, because of what happens in Action1 thread.

With this change, it is not only checked with DB if task has ended in
second transaction, but it also checks, if task was ended in the previous
transaction.

Closes-Bug: 1535722

Change-Id: Ifb2cfde4a88619b7664669f2d5ca14fa47379961

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-27 17:58:05.000000000', 'files': ['lib/puppet/provider/vs_port/ovs_redhat.rb'], 'message': 'Fix vs_port usage in Red Hat distros

Commit f39a4ca961ac1353b48c60d2c27aebba8ae1b2da moved constant
creation inside a do block to avoid duplication warnings, but at
the same time renamed them to self::BASE and self::DEFAULT, causing
issues when those variables where used elsewhere (e.g. in
lib/puppetx/redhat/ifcfg.rb).

Renaming those variables back and using ||= for assignment removes
the warning, while at the same time fixes the issues created by the
previous commit.

Change-Id: I3a02710811d91e141d56ab476dd32c3c7cf0ca80
'}]
commit_message:
Fix vs_port usage in Red Hat distros

Commit f39a4ca961ac1353b48c60d2c27aebba8ae1b2da moved constant
creation inside a do block to avoid duplication warnings, but at
the same time renamed them to self::BASE and self::DEFAULT, causing
issues when those variables where used elsewhere (e.g. in
lib/puppetx/redhat/ifcfg.rb).

Renaming those variables back and using ||= for assignment removes
the warning, while at the same time fixes the issues created by the
previous commit.

Change-Id: I3a02710811d91e141d56ab476dd32c3c7cf0ca80

commit_message:
Add access rule deletion waiter to tempest plugin

tempest.clients_share call wait_for_resource_deletion
does not accept acccess-rule ids and there is no other
call for waiting for access-rule deletion.

As bug descriptions says, one use case is, if we delete
an access rule and try to mount the share on nas client.
In case mount via ssh is faster than access rule deletion,
we might get false results and then this wait function
is required.

Hence creating same.

Change-Id: I099bdf66eb5e5b6468fde275754694638304cf10
Closes-Bug: #1429952
Depends-On: I3f1b109621f3ef72b1b9415e7da9d2cefb7c9000

commit_message:
Consolidate externall shell execs

Individual subprocess Popen and communicate calls are
now directed through utils.execute() method.

Fixed gateway deletion shell command in case there is
a metric in the command output.

Closes-Bug: #1514387

commit_message:
A minor modification of the Deployment Guide

In the section of General Service Tuning, there is a sentence
"Our Storage servers all run together on the same servers".
The word "servers" is used twice with different meanings, which
would be a little confusing. This patch makes it more understandable.

Closes-Bug: #1526697

commit_message:
Make 'cast' calls to Scheduler RPC API asynchronous

Now, RPC Client 'cast' method hangs if RabbitMQ is down.
So we can move such call to green threads to make our API faster.
We don't need to return results from 'cast' calls, it will be
None for any method.

Change-Id: I7ae8980ecd9fbb8168bed6a41ed37fef535f145a
Closes-Bug: #1539057
Related-Bug: #1539058

In addition, enable new setup for vmware-nsx and ironic-inspector - the

commit_message:
Use new translation setup for all python projects

Use the new translation setup for all python projects. This now uses
it for most python projects and those will just work without any change
with the new setup since for them modulename and reponame are the same.
For example for nova, both are "nova".

In addition, enable new setup for vmware-nsx and ironic-inspector - the
projects are ready now.

Note this change temporarily disables python-novaclient and
python-neutronclient - instead of making the script complicated, we wait
until all python projects are ready and then reenable all.

This also removes the old propose_python function that is not needed
anymore and renames propose_python_new to propose_python.

Remove also some outdated comments.

Story: 2000452
Change-Id: I5b89f7b168a862773282dc0400763b1a94ea9e10

commit_message:
Enhance manager list_role_assignments to support group listing

With the enahnced list_role_assignment manager method we have
already removed most of the duplication of inheritance logic when
listing roles. However, for federated operations there was a
class of query focused around assignments that derive from the
set of groups (i.e. those a federation user is given membership
of) that was not supported by list_role_assignments.

This patch adds that support, removes the duplicative
driver methods and re-implements the manager methods to call
list_role_assignments.

Implements: blueprint assignment-manager-cleanup
Change-Id: I9d76878963b178ec474b0c89be2ad2024bdd10d5

commit_message:
Load several fixtures when tesing

This patch makes it possible to load several fixtures
into nailgun database before starting tests.
One can use NAILGUN_FIXTURE_FILES variable.
It is to be a space separated list of files that
are then to be used together with 'manage.py loaddata'
command.

Closes-Bug: #1540421

commit_message:
zuul/layout: optimize puppet jobs

This patch aims to optimize the consumtion of OpenStack Infra for Puppet
OpenStack jobs.

It will avoid to run some jobs if we're just patching *.md files or
releasenotes managed by reno.

Here are the job we want to skip:
* gate-puppet-.*-puppet-syntax-.*-dsvm-.*
* gate-puppet-.*-puppet-unit-.*-dsvm-.*
* gate-puppet-.*-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-.*
* gate-puppet-openstack-integration-scenario00(1|2)-tempest-dsvm-.*

Which are syntax, unit & functional testing jobs.

It will save a lot of resources when we just want to update releasenotes
or doc.

Change-Id: I300abb47259a6fa9acdcfbc3e2eb15f9c3fea69b

commit_message:
[Core-Library] Fix the way of getting DNS in describe() method

This patch changes the method of getting dns address.
Previously dns could be an empty list, if user didn't configured
'default_dns' settings in murano.conf. Now it is taken from already
created subnet.

subject: Update translation setup
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-28 22:08:37.000000000', 'files': ['neutron-lib/locale/neutron-lib.pot', 'neutron_lib/_i18n.py', 'setup.cfg'], 'message': "Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
neutron-lib/locale/neutron-lib.pot to
neutron_lib/locale/neutron_lib.pot. For this we need to update
setup.cfg.

Update also domain name in _i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

Change-Id: I73db7b37f5a44ae45c01ca16abccb41a5fbfbfe8
"}]
commit_message:
Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
neutron-lib/locale/neutron-lib.pot to
neutron_lib/locale/neutron_lib.pot. For this we need to update
setup.cfg.

Update also domain name in _i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

commit_message:
Remove duplicated take_action logging

This commit drops utils.log_method decorators.
As a result of logging refactoring in openstackclient [1],
utils.log_method decorator is no longer used in openstackclient
and we are planning to drop utils.log_method.

searchlightclient is the only project that uses log_method
decorator. take_action logging is duplicated, so we can safely
drop log_method decorator.

Once this patch is merged, openstackclient can drop utils.log_method
because there is no released searchlightclient.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/q/topic:bug/1532294

Change-Id: Ib94e7ba77262a9a8cbfce71f3083c47cb1973364
Related-Bug: #1532294

commit_message:
Limit keystone extension tests for the existing

Since Ifac71f7415f21c402f6e00c5264e972b0e80388c in Mitaka, the
os_inherit of Keystone is enable on the default config.
In addition, Tempest is branchless now.

So we need to limit keystone extension tests as the existing
ones(OS-EC2) for stable branch.

commit_message:
API: Rearrange HTTPBadRequest raising in _resize

This patch aimed to fix AutoDiskConfigDisabledByImage exception is
excpeced for 2 times, besides, rearrange HTTPBadRequest to group them
around each other for easy reading.

P.S. Don't touch any logic so no UT need to be added/changed.

Closes-Bug: #1538411

Closes-Bug: #1539355
'}]
commit_message:
Fix ValueError in allocate_unique_key in Zookeeper

When calling ensure_path, it will create the key
without value, which causes ValueError.

The ensure_path should not be invoked in this
function, because the function is able to deal with
NoNodeError.

Change-Id: Ib73828ed71f1ed9fad94b0a323097fa76bb20241
Closes-Bug: #1539355

Disable NetworkManager by default

commit_message:
add return in for-loop in unbind_router_servicenode

Previous method unbind_router_servicenode will return True for
case port related to a router still exists on servicenode. In
that case, it makes no sense not to directly return True, but
keep method running its left part.

This patch will add return to fix details mentioned above, for
that, variable port_found is no longer necessary to use. And
redefine return value, False for notification was not sent case,
which means unbind_router_servicenode should not work successfully,
otherwise return True.

Change-Id: I8d877fb2f73988381a03642b92c3220192089e27

revisions:

I've found that given a sufficiently bad replica2part2dev table we can

It shows up most on > 3 replica rings when you have two *different*

Change-Id: Ieb213c1a259815a2ed657291242919cda568c7b5

commit_message:
Always fix devices with multiple part-replica assignments

I've found that given a sufficiently bad replica2part2dev table we can
accidently not entirely fix palcement when more than two replicas of a
part are assigned to the duplicate devices.

It shows up most on > 3 replica rings when you have two *different*
devices both holding two replicas.  But you can see it on a three
replica ring when all three replicas are assigned to the same device.

Change-Id: Ieb213c1a259815a2ed657291242919cda568c7b5

commit_message:
Remove bindings of DVR routers to L3 agents on compute nodes

As described in the spec there is no need to explicitly bind
DVR router to each l3 agent running on compute nodes where
there are dvr serviceable ports - this brings complexity to the code,
makes it less readable and very hard to maintain (one could see how many
bugs were filed and fixed regarding dvr scheduling stuff already).
Also this brings scalability problems as time needed for router scheduling
grows linearly with the number of compute nodes.

The idea is to align dvr scheduling with legacy router scheduling:
only schedule SNAT portion of the router and use DB queries whenever
we need to know which compute nodes should host the router.

Implements blueprint improve-dvr-l3-agent-binding

Change-Id: I82c8d256c56bb16cdc1b1232ebb660d09909f9c6

I was asked if dogpile.cache.memcached was recommended for Apache httpd
with mod_wsgi because our docs did not make it clear that
dogpile.cache_memcached_pool wasn't necessary. This patch adds an
explicit recommendation.

Along the way, I also cleaned up a few RST formatting issues and
consistently referred to "Apache httpd with ``mod_wsgi``", which is how
Apache *usually* does it themselves (sometimes HTTPD is in all caps, but

'}]
commit_message:
Update mod_wsgi + cache config docs

I was asked if dogpile.cache.memcached was recommended for Apache httpd
with mod_wsgi because our docs did not make it clear that
dogpile.cache_memcached_pool wasn't necessary. This patch adds an
explicit recommendation.

Along the way, I also cleaned up a few RST formatting issues and
consistently referred to "Apache httpd with ``mod_wsgi``", which is how
Apache *usually* does it themselves (sometimes HTTPD is in all caps, but
it's never a literal like module names are).

Change-Id: Ic562853bacc13f70712e0e61f8aeb8dffc75ab2e

commit_message:
Fix showing network quotas for a project

The OpenStack SDK is now used for the network client. However,
the 'openstack quota show' command wasn't updated for the
client change. As a result, the command will fail to show
network quotas when a project name is specified. For example:

  $ openstack quota show admin
  'Proxy' object has no attribute 'show_quota'

This patch set fixes the command by using the OpenStack SDK
to get network quotas for a project.

Change-Id: I59a7b6780a7b80cd09e79d40d214751b25d3016e
Related-To: blueprint neutron-client
Closes-Bug: #1528249

commit_message:
Baremetal migration

When a baremetal node is broken, it should be migrated into other
redundant node. This feature should also depend on the improvement
in Ironic story which will be implemented by the following Ironic BP.
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/ironic/+spec/bare-metal-node-n+1-redundancy

And this spec will implement the integration of Ironic and nova about
this feature. i.e. it will meet the step-1 of blueprint
baremetal-migration-evacuation.

Change-Id: I2f6a4e66a7a62b41d66e13f6b9a953d5dd31c76e
Depends-on: I3776dd497e6b1d8cf4f7e59f8663d9d787c8d1f1
Implements: blueprint baremetal-migration-evacuation
Co-Authored-By: Tang Chen <tangchen@cn.fujitsu.com>

Change-Id: I1939281d844336accb8e7776dddb68a536ef281a

commit_message:
log take_action parameters in a single place

Previously each command logs take_action parameters explicitly
by using @utils.log_method decorator or log.debug().
Some commands have no logging.

This commit calls a logger in the base class and
drops all logging definition from individual commands.

Closes-Bug: #1532294
Change-Id: I43cd0290a4353c68c075bade9571c940733da1be

subject: Add POST method for creating pools and flavors
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-02 01:58:43.000000000', 'files': ['specs/mitaka/post-method-pools-flavors.rst'], 'message': "Add POST method for creating pools and flavors

For now the only way to create a pool or flavor is to use PUT method,
which can accidentally update the existing pool or flavor.
If we implement HTTP POST method for creating pools and flavors, the
user who doesn't want to accidentally overwrite the existing resource,
would be able to use POST method instead of PUT method.

Change-Id: I168d72220d79c3046dce3b0e36b24967d57083d5
Implements: blueprint post-method-pools-flavors
"}]
commit_message:
Add POST method for creating pools and flavors

For now the only way to create a pool or flavor is to use PUT method,
which can accidentally update the existing pool or flavor.
If we implement HTTP POST method for creating pools and flavors, the
user who doesn't want to accidentally overwrite the existing resource,
would be able to use POST method instead of PUT method.

Change-Id: I168d72220d79c3046dce3b0e36b24967d57083d5
Implements: blueprint post-method-pools-flavors

commit_message:
Bandit profile updates

We'd like to use the same "gate" profile for all OpenStack gate jobs,
so the "keystone_conservative" profile which we were running as part
of the gate is change to "gate.

The other profiles that aren't used as part of the gate are removed.

commit_message:
Refactor parts of failure resolving/handling

Instead of having the completer also contain the
strategy resolving logic have it instead just have a
mapping of outcomes -> failure resolvers and have those
failure resolvers do the work of actually resolving
any failures that occur.

It also removes the double isinstance check and
handling of failures by using the already existing
isinstance check to call into different completion
methods (one for failures and one for not).

Change-Id: I71ee3068ce6b33c88a6596b60260a28d4fa87872

commit_message:
remove unnecessary message when running unit test

When we test log related code, we still print the tested log message
into stderr, which is not quite useful for developers, we should
mock those message. Package fixtures.FakeLogger already provides an
option to mock specified logger, so let's use it.

Note: this patch also changes an unnecessary object attribute to local
varible.

Change-Id: I4bc5beaa4eba149f12c58f072fe66163aed8c0c8
Closes-Bug: #1500236

commit_message:
Spec for trust

Some services which are running in a bay need to access OpenStack
services. In order to access OpenStack services, we can create a
trustee for each bay and delegate a limited set of rights to the
trustee.

Partially-Implements: blueprint create-trustee-user-for-each-bay

Add conductor manager to handle all RPC handler

This patch introduces a new class ConductorManager which will be in charge
for the RPC_API_VERSION controller.

We have plan to make some of rpc calling method to use async mode, this patch

commit_message:
allow DHCP from router interfaces

DHCP. This supports the Astara appliance case where DHCP is running
within the same appliance providing routing.

Backported from commit 1b3e6dd1a5336009c274083c2a25c2285d379e6

commit_message:
Pass network_id to ML2 type drivers.

This patch enhances the call to Type Drivers to include network ID.

commit_message:
fix locking in ceilometer

there are quite a few things wrong with current implementation.
- pop doesn't call __delitem__. not sure why but basically it's not
getting called. ever.
- cannot set blocking=False when using contextmanager. blocking=False
can only be done by calling acquire(False)

this fixes both cases above so now locks are actually deleted.

Change-Id: I171862815ee3abe8c10441bdb85ff7c1ee547ed0

commit_message:
Replace unicode with six.text_type

The Unicode type is 'unicode' in Python 2 and 'str' on Python 3.
This patch replaces unicode with six.text_type to make Keystone
compatible with Python 2 and Python 3. To protect against regression
two py34 problems were fixed and test_middleware.py was added
to tox.ini.

Co-Authored-By: Tom Cocozzello <tjcocozz@us.ibm.com>
bp python3
Change-Id: I4a5cf86ca1aa5f4d305696c2b39cdbc7e2cbc71e

commit_message:
Move rabbit conf settings to separate section

oslo.messaging has deprecated the use of messaging config settings,
specifically rabbit_* settings, in the [DEFAULT] section. This commit
moves the rabbit settings to a [oslo_messaging_rabbit] section in
each of the relevant trove service sample config files.

Change-Id: Ia869768102a8a841313cd7e0fd8a9fdab257d3e3
Closes-Bug: #1528391

commit_message:
Add fixed_subnet to Baymodel Object

In current Magnum code, Baymodel's 'fixed_network' is mapped to heat's
'fixed_network_cidr'. So 'fixed_network' actually means 'fixed_network_cidr',
or more precisely 'fixed_subnet'. For heat stack creation, it need
create a new fixed network and fixed subnet. So, give 'fixed_network'
the role it should be, and add a new field 'fixed_subnet' to Baymodel,
and then use 'fixed_subnet' to take the place of current 'fixed_network'.
This patch add fixed_subnet in Baymodel to support this.

Change-Id: Ia74ed924b3058b4891775f34f1b9624774c02ddb
Partial-Bug: #1519748

commit_message:
Raise exception when Bay Failed

Raise a BayException when Bay create/update/delete failed with
detail status and failure reason. This make more louder noises when
error occurred, so it's more easier for users to locate them.

commit_message:
Add registry_address to bay db and api

User can know the docker registry url by registry_address. When a user
want to pull or push a image from registry, he should add the
registry_address before the image name and tag like
docker pull ${registry_name}/${image_name}:${image_tag}
docker push ${registry_name}/${image_name}:${image_tag}.

Partially-Implements: blueprint registryv2-in-master

commit_message:
Use trusts for TLS cert generation

Currently, we use the users auth token, which expires after a while.
We need to use a trust_id instead.

- This patch adds trusts support for swarm and kubernetes bays.
- Modified keystone to authenticate using a trust_id and generate a
trust token.
- Update devstack setup to create a tls role to the demo and admin
users for functional testing.

Closes-bug: #1503863
Change-Id: I18162485575794e533fbcbac5fec3790b4d37c64

commit_message:
Add template definition testing

Bug 1496110 was caused by a difference between the outputs of the
template definition and the heat template's outputs. This change adds
tests for each template definition. The outputs are tested to be a
subset of the outputs for the associated heat template.

Change-Id: I654ef592db8e31f249cd18f0f5fb28ebe237a31b
Closes-Bug: #1496572
Related-Bug: #1496110

raise coordination error if not registered

in the scenario where an agent does not get registered in group,
try to rejoin group. if not successful after 5 attempts, give up
and raise.

commit_message:
Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
python-keystoneclient/locale/python-keystoneclient.pot to
keystoneclient/locale/keystoneclient.pot. For this we need to update
setup.cfg. The domain name is already correct in keystoneclient/_i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

Change-Id: Ie5a0c3e8fcdb485edf05f2188fce64a9fce96b5f

commit_message:

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
python-novaclient/locale/python-novaclient.pot to
novaclient/locale/novaclient. For this we need to update
setup.cfg. The domain name is already correct in
novaclient/i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

commit_message:
Update translation setup

Follow new infra setup for translations, see spec
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack-infra/infra-specs/specs/translation_setup.html
for full details.

This basically renames
ironic-inspector/locale/ironic-inspector.pot to
ironic_inspector/locale/ironic_inspector.pot. For this we need to update
setup.cfg. Also fix some errors for translation setup in setup.cfg

Update also domain name in i18n.py.

The project has no translations currently, let's remove the outdated
pot file, the updated scripts work without them. So, we can just
delete the file and once there are translations, an updated pot file
together with translations can be imported automatically.

Change-Id: I1f9e3777a68d09406eeee836d03f15cbfe568470

commit_message:
LeftHand: Add volume fail-back capabilities

This patch adds the ability to fail-back a volume after it has been
failed over to a managed or unmanaged target.

Because resynchronizing the primary and secondary volumes can take a
very long time, Cinder will not handle the resynchronization. Instead,
the operations should be conducted on the LeftHand arrays themselves
before the fail-back occurs in Cinder.

Change-Id: I7ac4855b0c65dca09bfe8965ac2fa66e5a9b1e2d

commit_message:
3PAR: Add volume fail-back capabilities

This patch adds the ability to fail-back a volume after it has been
failed over to a managed or unmanaged target.

Because resynchronizing the primary and secondary volumes can take a
very long time, Cinder will not handle the resynchronization. Instead,
the operations should be conducted on the 3PAR arrays themselves
before the fail-back occurs in Cinder.

This patch removes all the unit tests that were created to verify
replication actions could not be performed on non-replicated volumes
because this is now checked in the volume API.

Implements: blueprint hpe-3par-volume-failback
Change-Id: Ie7b80a15090c6fe7a4d5f61e7b11040362bf1cd2

commit_message:
remove argparse from requirements list

argparse is only needed as an external dependency for python 2.6, which
we no longer support. Including it seems to confuse pip 8.0, causing job
failures, so remove it here as a step in removing it from all of the
explicit lists of dependencies in all projects.

Change-Id: Ia57b9a341c977dece684f21f5fc458471a74e7f3
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Revert "Move default Keystone API version to v3"

It seems like the fallout from this was not well sorted.
A lot of things aren't working, and there is still vestigial
v2 bits left behind.

This should have come with a much greater warning and some
spot checking of additional services working with this.

This reverts commit b162a1d58cdecfb32847b59bd341e06c26efb1ed.

Change-Id: Ia792b23119c00089542ba08879dca1c29dc80945

commit_message:
Refactor pieces of noop testing framework

This patch does the following:

1) Adds puppet_spec library to a list of fetched
specs to leverage some of additional matchers
2) Makes spec_helper load puppet core spec directory
which may also contain things we would want to reuse
3) Introduces new matcher for transitive dependencies
that allows one to not search for exact dependencies
with `that_comes_before` matcher, but to just check for
resources dependencies

Change-Id: Iad3b6f31a4c5be1ec306d9b4e7eedbd2cf720e95
Related-bug: #1533279
(cherry picked from commit 9af54824e7431b5cb108c701be47286e7b10206a)

commit_message:
Switch auth_file URL generation to work properly

This fix actually passes a variable to openstack::auth_file
class which is using it then to interpolate it into
a string in openrc file. Otherwise we have an internal_url
which is improperly dereferenced and does not contain
suffix for the URI to choose the version

Change-Id: Ic3a70137e95df91c8e8fa257f16274e68075c800
Partial-bug: #1533588
Partial-bug: #1539644

commit_message:
Rakefile support for Git changes

This commit enables integration with Git. Now before run
RSpec or Lint tasks Rakefile will check for Git changes
and run these tasks on changed modules only otherwise
they ran against all modules.

Change-Id: I79ffbb8e2ed0c10cf03a1b2e176b75b314a3e79d
(cherry picked from commit f60d5ed950baefd2223388d66e71b7f037affffd)

Related-Bug: #1513900

commit_message:
Balance /var and /var/log disk partitions

Prior to Fuel 8.0, there was a balance of the
following directories for remaining space:
/var, /var/lib/docker, /var/log

Now docker has its own pv, and /var/log was
incorrectly given all the remaining space,
leaving /var fixed at 10GB.

The new balance is as follows:
docker pv: 20gb
/: 10gb fixed size
/var: 40% of remaining space
/var/log: 60% of remaining space

Also raised minimum disk space requirement to
45GB. This reflects the actual minimum sizes
so that a user receives the error before partitioning
and is properly informed.

Change-Id: Id283e7dd4b94d5f6e1eb8397af33fea2b9f985f7
Closes-Bug: #1540331

commit_message:
Fix instance not destroyed after successful evacuation

After complete evacuate action, the status of migration will change
to 'done' from 'accepted', so the _destroy_evacuated_instances action
in old nova-compute should consider the status 'done' to filter
migration list when they're back up.

Closes-bug: #1518200
Co-Authored-By: Sylvain Bauza <sbauza@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ie4825dcaa778d229922c963a96590ad5a2604257
(cherry picked from commit a79ac83bae4e673a416cca4b86a3f47f4f25b0aa)

commit_message:
Fix RequestSpec _from_db_object

The semantics of _from_db_update are that it should update the object
that is passed in since it it typically used within an object to update
itself.  RequestSpec._from_db_object was not updating the object that
was passed in and was essentially aliasing the parameter with a newly
created object.  This fixes it and updates the tests which worked
because they used _from_db_update in a different manner than it's used
in practice.

Change-Id: Ia516caceceddc1617b78871f699a7ad674fb044a

commit_message:
Skip identity v2 functional tests

DevStack now uses identity v3 by default thus causing OSC to
only load openstack.identity.v3 commands. This prevents running
functional tests on openstack.identity.v2 commands. As a result,
this patch set skips all identity v2 functional tests to unblock
the gate.

Change-Id: I066187318be71792a966fa21226fab0d406c3758
Partial-Bug: #1539780

commit_message:
Remove custom api-paste.ini for testing

It makes all tests pass throught paste.deploy instead of
the custom app loader in tests.

This change disable rados thread system, that just slow down metricd.

'}]
commit_message:
Disable rados thread system

This change disable rados thread system, that just slow down metricd.

A quick example of performance gain: http://paste.openstack.org/show/485202/

The side effect of removing this thread is that a SIGINT during a
Ceph API call will be handled only when the call is ended.

https://github.com/ceph/ceph/commit/2ce5cb7d06c80e34824981c36adcaa2dbfbc581f

Future version of python-rados should move to cython instead of ctypes
and should not thread and suffer of this issue.

Change-Id: I3dfc04f49df0129eaaa3f1ebb1917efbea9b5355
(cherry picked from commit d33def9246e5b961bbeae4ee8e105e10ecabfa04)

commit_message:
Add subjectAltName to generated ssl cert

SSL certs generated by "keystone-manage ssl_setup" do not provide
subjectAuthName.  This results in a warning with each response.
The sample_data script fails to cope with this.
- Added Multi string opt to the [ssl] section of the config file to
allow a subjectAltName field to be specified in the certs generated
in the form of fqdn, hostname or ip address.
- Added 'subject_alt_names' to [signing] section in config as
this is used to generate certs too.
- Updated test fixtures to include subject_alt_names.
- Added tests to verify that generated certificates have the
  subject_alt_names include.

Closes-Bug #1419825

Change-Id: Ia47edd035aa6a27e94a00bb47aad35e754bee517

commit_message:
Adjust build script to not use rev-parse

The gate's post-jobs run from a detached head. Using rev-parse yields
the last commit of master as opposed to the newly merged commit.
Use and parse git-log instead.

Change-Id: I2c4d8501191a95005e566f2c594a3d880b688096
(cherry picked from commit 101859e2b4db0ae8d262cb0b8e901d800275a8d7)

commit_message:
Explicitly delete DHCP ports in delete_network.

We've been seeing a lot of tempest failures in many different tests due
to failing to delete a network because ports are still in use.  Trying
to debug it has shown some pretty bizarre results.

This patch is one thing that I tried and it seems to help.  I've
rechecked it >10 times and haven't seen the failure happen again.

I'm absolutely not confident that this is a complete or correct fix.
The best I can say is that it's at least closer to how the ML2 plugin
behaves.

Change-Id: Ia1a4f23f74768a4ab6315429b940525386342b16
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-01 16:26:07.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/db/db_base_plugin_v2.py'], 'message': "Sync session when auto deleting DHCP ports.

The tempest job for networking-ovn has been failing a decent amount on
NetworkInUse errors when trying to delete a network.  Trying to debug
this has shown some very odd results.

Digging into this further, the base plugin attempts to automatically
delete DHCP ports.  However, the ML2 plugin has a cleanup while loop in
delete_network() which deletes these ports manually.  Adding a similar
manual delete into networking-ovn has made the error disappear so far.

The method used to auto delete DHCP ports in the base plugin uses
synchronize_session=False, which seems like it could lead to unexpected
behavior when working with ports later in the same session.  For more
info, see the sqlalchemy docs here:

    http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/orm/query.html

This patch changes synchronize_session from False to 'fetch'.
'evaluate' will raise an error in this case.

Change-Id: I8b1be69d45c5d3cce0ebb19f37287f071482b741
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>
"}]
commit_message:
Sync session when auto deleting DHCP ports.

The tempest job for networking-ovn has been failing a decent amount on
NetworkInUse errors when trying to delete a network.  Trying to debug
this has shown some very odd results.

Digging into this further, the base plugin attempts to automatically
delete DHCP ports.  However, the ML2 plugin has a cleanup while loop in
delete_network() which deletes these ports manually.  Adding a similar
manual delete into networking-ovn has made the error disappear so far.

The method used to auto delete DHCP ports in the base plugin uses
synchronize_session=False, which seems like it could lead to unexpected
behavior when working with ports later in the same session.  For more
info, see the sqlalchemy docs here:

    http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/orm/query.html

This patch changes synchronize_session from False to 'fetch'.
'evaluate' will raise an error in this case.

Change-Id: I8b1be69d45c5d3cce0ebb19f37287f071482b741
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Set config values and fix casual failing of nc service in scenario tests

1. Set the config values to make it work against non-devstack environment
2  Tweak webserver script, use nc "l" for listening to avoid clients to hang
waiting for the connection close after the content has been served when
using cirros 0.3.3 image. In Cirros 0.3.3, nc doesn't support "-ll" option
for persistence listening

Change-Id: Iecf70014f9444b226a0b08971e1c2ac26f653257
Closes-Bug: #1538746

commit_message:
Fix rerun of task in subworkflow

If rerunning a task of sub-workflow, the sub-workflow completes successfully
but the main workflow remains in ERROR. The method set_execution_state in
workflow handler is modified to reset the upstream parent task and workflow
states on resume and re-run.

Change-Id: I8d04305277b8ec18193c07cf80474ef7168f2627
Closes-Bug: #1535926

commit_message:
Set hpcloud max-servers to -1

In preparation for the sunset of hpcloud's public cloud stop building
images and running tests on hpcloud. This will force nodepool to cleanup
after itself in hpcloud prior to the sunset there. Once this is done we
can remove hpcloud from the configuration entirely.

Change-Id: I159a074791f4fa552e3dfa2c4eda39daaa330d18

subject: Use raw data storage for events to collect more info
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-01-27 13:40:00.000000000', 'files': ['osprofiler/parsers/ceilometer.py', 'osprofiler/tests/parsers/test_ceilometer.py'], 'message': 'Use raw data storage for events to collect more info

OSprofiler uses free-form notifications in fact, so any kind of data
might be included to the profiling trace. To be able to do that in
Ceilometer case, that use explicit event definitions, we need to
use its raw data events storage, that will include all notification
message.

To use this feature the following section needs to be set in
ceilometer.conf:

[event]
store_raw = info

where info is the notification level used.

Warning: if raw data is used, ALL events that come into ceilometer
with info notification level will be stored with raw data included,
there is no way to set this parameter only for profiler.* events.

Change-Id: I3ebf8ee34ac01e68d530a676ae840f7a62d897bd
'}]
commit_message:
Use raw data storage for events to collect more info

OSprofiler uses free-form notifications in fact, so any kind of data
might be included to the profiling trace. To be able to do that in
Ceilometer case, that use explicit event definitions, we need to
use its raw data events storage, that will include all notification
message.

To use this feature the following section needs to be set in
ceilometer.conf:

[event]
store_raw = info

where info is the notification level used.

Warning: if raw data is used, ALL events that come into ceilometer
with info notification level will be stored with raw data included,
there is no way to set this parameter only for profiler.* events.

Change-Id: I3ebf8ee34ac01e68d530a676ae840f7a62d897bd
